{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":49567,"duration_api_ms":49532,"num_turns":10,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ee529a40-7e74-4b0a-9d69-2810aaabc42f","total_cost_usd":0.30328049999999995,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25760,"cache_read_input_tokens":185191,"output_tokens":1986,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":25760,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":1986,"cacheReadInputTokens":185191,"cacheCreationInputTokens":25760,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.30328049999999995,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All four amendments target real aspects of plan_hash provenance handling. Three identify genuine bugs with clear fix paths; one (fr-11-fb2ec5ae) identifies a known, documented trade-off that is already acknowledged in code comments and represents conscious design debt rather than an overlooked defect.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-11-8183a7c6","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by reading safe_plan_hash_backfill at fs.rs:2628-2649. Line 2639 returns false when snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation is None, treating 'no plan existed yet' identically to 'legacy entry with unknown provenance'. These are semantically different: a 'no plan yet' entry has known empty provenance that can safely be upgraded when a plan later arrives, because there is no prior plan version to conflict with. The proposed fix — allowing backfill when both plan_hash and snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation are None AND the entry is still Running — is safe and addresses a real gap in the acceptance criterion. The new entry creation at line 3071 sets snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation to current_snapshot_hash, which is None when no plan has been persisted yet, confirming this scenario is reachable."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-fb2ec5ae","decision":"reject","rationale":"The code at fs.rs:3054-3059 already contains an explicit comment documenting this exact race as a 'Known limitation' and stating the long-term fix is for callers to supply plan_hash explicitly. This is conscious, documented design debt, not an overlooked bug. The race window between dispatch and record_task_run_start is narrow. Threading dispatch-time plan hash through every call path is a significant architectural change inappropriate for a targeted amendment. The existing comment ensures the issue is tracked and discoverable."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-4bfe4027","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by reading fs.rs:3002-3030. Lines 3009-3010 use entries.iter().position() to find the first raw row matching same_attempt, but in duplicate-row states the first raw row can be the stale copy with plan_hash=None. The canonical view (from collapse_task_run_group via merge_attempt_entries) would have the populated metadata from another duplicate, but the code operates on the potentially stale raw row. backfill_running_entry and safe_plan_hash_backfill then operate on this stale row, potentially finding nothing to change. Line 3033 then returns the canonical existing_entry (which has merged metadata) but the raw file is never repaired. The fix should either use canonical entry metadata to inform the raw row repair, or select the most complete duplicate as the repair target."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-60e3c49b","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by reading merge_attempt_entries at model.rs:320-337. The function merges run_id (line 323), plan_hash (line 326), outcome_detail (line 329), started_at (line 331), and finished_at (lines 332-335) — but completely omits snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation. Both collapse_task_run_group (model.rs:641) and duplicate cleanup (fs.rs:3310-3314) call merge_attempt_entries. If the primary row has snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation=None and a secondary duplicate has the provenance, the merge permanently drops it. After that, safe_plan_hash_backfill at fs.rs:2639 sees None and refuses to backfill, breaking the entire repair chain. The fix is straightforward: add the same None-coalescing pattern used for the other fields."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a07deba8-8961-4a7b-8ebe-ca20112f25a3"}
